{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 20:29:48.764783", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and Goal\\n- Topology: 2 leaves (leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1), 2 spines (spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1), 1 super-spine (super_spine_router_0), 2 hosts (pc_0_0, pc_0_1). EBGP-only Clos fabric; hosts on 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 subnets.\\n- Objective: Assess network health, detect anomalies, localize faulty device(s), and identify root cause.\\n\\nSummary of Findings\\n- Control plane (BGP): Healthy across all routers.\\n- Data plane: Severe packet loss affecting traffic to/from pc_0_0. pc_0_1 path is normal.\\n- Root cause: Host-side traffic corruption configured on pc_0_0 eth0 via tc netem (corrupt 60%).\\n\\nDetails and Evidence\\n\\n1) Reachability and Loss\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1:\\n  - 20 pings, 65% loss, avg RTT ~2.78 ms.\\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0:\\n  - 10 pings, 70% loss, avg RTT ~3.38 ms.\\n- pc_0_0 -> its default gateway (leaf_router_0_0 172.16.0.33):\\n  - 10 pings, 60% loss, sub-1 ms RTT on received replies.\\n- pc_0_1 -> its default gateway (leaf_router_0_1 172.16.0.35):\\n  - 10 pings, 0% loss, ~0.84 ms avg RTT.\\n\\nInterpretation:\\n- Loss exists even on the first L3 hop from pc_0_0 to its leaf, pointing to an issue on or very near pc_0_0.\\n- pc_0_1 path shows no local loss, suggesting fabric and leaf_router_0_1 are normal.\\n\\n2) Host Interface/Queueing State\\n- pc_0_0 eth0:\\n  - tc qdisc show dev eth0: qdisc netem ... corrupt 60%\\n  - tc -s qdisc show dev eth0: netem corrupt 60% (counters present)\\n  - ip addr shows qdisc netem on eth0.\\n- pc_0_1 eth0:\\n  - tc qdisc show dev eth0: qdisc fq_codel (normal; no netem).\\n\\nInterpretation:\\n- A 60% packet corruption rate on pc_0_0’s egress will cause many L3 packets (e.g., ICMP) to fail checksum and be dropped, manifesting as high loss in both directions (echo replies from pc_0_0 are corrupted; requests from pc_0_0 are also corrupted).\\n\\n3) Control Plane Health (BGP)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1: All EBGP neighbors Established; State/PfxRcd populated.\\n- spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: All EBGP neighbors Established; routes to leaves and super-spine present.\\n- super_spine_router_0: EBGP neighbors Established to spines.\\n- Routing tables on all routers include expected /24 host networks via EBGP next-hops; connected /31s consistent across inter-router links.\\n\\nInterpretation:\\n- No indications of BGP session flaps, stuck states, or missing routes. Control plane appears stable and consistent.\\n\\nAnomaly Detection\\n- Abnormal behavior: High packet loss (60–70%) on traffic involving pc_0_0, including to its own default gateway.\\n- Normal behavior: pc_0_1 edge and upstream links show 0% loss to its leaf; router BGP adjacencies and RIBs look healthy.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_0\\n- Faulty component: eth0 queuing discipline\\n- Evidence: tc netem configured with “corrupt 60%” on pc_0_0 eth0; correlates directly with ~60–70% packet loss observed from/to pc_0_0 and even to its first hop.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Artificial packet corruption injected by tc netem on pc_0_0 eth0 (corrupt 60%) causing widespread loss of packets due to checksum errors.\\n- Fabric (leaves/spines/super-spine) control and data planes exhibit normal routing and reachability for unaffected paths.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- Traffic to/from pc_0_0 is severely degraded (approx. 60–70% loss).\\n- Traffic via pc_0_1 and across the Clos fabric otherwise appears healthy based on tests performed and BGP/route state.\\n\\nNo remediation steps are proposed in this report per instructions., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='f8f60809-31ea-432e-8902-d17eade649c6'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
